All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Autograde  
    Cell
    This class represents a single cell in the cell transmission model.
    CentroidConnector
    This class models a centroid connector (no capacity constraint, no density constraint).
    CTM
    This class propagates flow according to the cell transmission model.
    Diverge
    This class represents a diverge: where 1 upstream link branches out into 2 or more downstream links.
    Link
    This represents a link in the network.
    LTM
    This class propagates flow according to the link transmission model.
    Main
    This is the Main class.
    Merge
    This class represents a merge: where 2 or more upstream links combine into 1 downstream link.
    MN  
    Network
    This class represents and stores the entire network, including the sets of Nodes and Links.
    Node
    This represents a node in the network.
    Params
    This class stores important global parameters that are useful across the entire project.
    Path
    This class represents a path, which is an ordered list of Links.
    PedSignal
    This class models 2 links in series, but the links are separated by a traffic light used to provide access to pedestrians.
    Phase
    This represents a single signal phase.
    PointQueue
    This class propagates flow according to the point queue model (no spatial constraints).
    ReadNetwork  
    Series
    This Node type simply connects two links, possibly with different capacities.
    Signal
    This class is used to model a traffic signal.
    Sink
    This class models behavior at a sink (at a destination node): all vehicles reaching the sink are removed from the network.
    Source
    This class models a source (origin node): vehicles spawn at this location at predetermined rates.
    SpatialQueue
    This class propagates flow according to the spatial queue model, including capacity constraints and a density constraint per link.
    StopSign
    This class models the equal priority intersection discussed in class.
